event.name: The Album Leaf Live in KL

version.name: The Album Leaf Live in KL
version.short-description: The music of The Album Leaf has been described as "celestial", "ethereal", "lustrous" and having a "calm ferocity"...
version.description:
The Album Leaf is the solo project of Jimmy LaValle, a San Diego-based songwriter who began recording solo material one year after forming the post-rock band Tristeza. Inspired by a number of genres -- classical, jazz, and post-rock among them -- LaValle constructed his own songs in a similarly eclectic manner, utilizing everything from ambient noise to field recordings to radio transmissions.

The music of The Album Leaf has been described as "celestial", "ethereal", "lustrous" and having a "calm ferocity" in recordings. But performing live, the act creates a soundscape and vibe on a whole new level of experience.

Now you can experience this yourself when they performs live in KL on 7 September. For further details, please contact booking@soundscape-records.com.
version.price: RM98 (Pre-sale) - Before 5th Sept / RM120 (At the door). Available at participating Rock Corner outlets

event.name: Critical Ingredients to Unlimited Success - CANCELLED

version.name: Critical Ingredients to Unlimited Success - CANCELLED
version.short-description: For the first time in Asia, revered management thinkers and best selling authors, James Suroweicki and Malcolm Gladwell, will challenge...
version.description:
UPDATE: EVENT CANCELLED. Go to the official website for more information.

For the first time in Asia, catch revered management thinkers and best selling authors, James Suroweicki and Malcolm Gladwell, who will challenge Malaysia audiences to think beyond their conventional views about leadership and success.
 
James Suroweicki will be discussing the 'Wisdom of Crowds' and 'The Future of Leadership', and explain how to get people to work better together, and strategies for turning collective knowledge into a true competitive advantage.
 
Malcolm Gladwell will then take you on a journey to the world of 'Outliers' which is the best and the brightest, the most famous and the most successful. Malcolm Gladwell will be examining what makes high achievers different and how you can learn from their experiences to achieve greatness in your own world.

Through sharing remarkable insights and factors that contribute to high levels of success, both personally and professionally, this is going to be an enriching seminar for reflecting and charting of what people need to do in work and life.

version.short-description: My English Teachers displays the EXTREME, the FUNNY and the WEIRD English teachers, through the eyes of three friends...
version.description:
My English Teachers displays the EXTREME, the FUNNY and the WEIRD English teachers, through the eyes of three friends. Returning with part two, the show takes on a different turn (NOT a sequel).

Synopsis:
2 friends, Akmal, who hails from some remote part of Kelantan and YY, who comes from a Chinese village, join a private college in KL for further education.

They meet Micson, who makes fun of them because of their poor English. Micson teaches Akmal and YY dirty words and plays practical jokes on them.

The boys also meet, Evon and Finaz, who look down upon the boys.

One day, the 2 boys chance upon a magic lamp and they invoke a genie. The genie grants them a few wishes but the boys turn all the wishes down. They request that the genie teach them English and punish the bullies instead.

The genie takes various forms and helps them master the English language and take revenge against Micson and the girls.

version.name: ApSci Live @ Laundry
version.short-description: ApSci was born out of the experimental hip hop communities from New York and Sydney...
version.description:
Opening acts by Figure of Speech and Zalila Lee.

ApSci was born out of the experimental hip hop communities from New York and Sydney by Raphael LaMotta and Dana Diaz-Tutaan in the late 1990's. The two met outside the well-loved club Baby Jupiter in the L.E.S. during a street cypher.

ApSci toured Australia, playing clubs anywhere from 1,000 down to 200 capacity. The live set now included monster drummer Guy Licata (Hercules & Love Affair, Santogold, Bill Laswell) on the stage.

ApSci have performed music festivals like Austin's South by South-West Music Festival in 2008, France's Eurokeennes to 10,000 kids alongside Spank Rock, The Strokes and Depeche Mode; through to bringing in New Years Eve to a healthy crowd of 15,000 strong at Pyramid Rock Festival in Australia in 2008.

version.name: 30 Hour Famine SS2 DIY Camp
version.short-description: 30 Hour Famine SS2 DIY Camp is a charity event focusing on urban poverty. With the theme, 'Light Up Their Life!', this 30 hours campaign aims to raise RM1million and all donations will be channeled to local NGOs and World Vision partnerships that serves to decrease poverty...
version.description:
30 Hour Famine SS2 DIY Camp is a charity event focusing on urban poverty. With the theme, 'Light Up Their Life!', this 30 hours campaign aims to raise RM1million and all donations will be channeled to local NGOs and World Vision partnerships that serves to decrease poverty.

What does 30 Hour Famine do?
Participants are required to fast for 26 hours while learning about global poverty issues and through games, activities and videos. The last 4 hours are spent at the Stadium Putra Bukit Jalil, Kuala Lumpur, where participants will have breakfast together. This is where all the other participants from all over the country will assemble and join in the Famine Countdown event.

Date:  21st August 2010
Time: 9.30am
Venue: SJK(C)Puay Chai

And

Date: 22nd August 2010
Time: After the 26 hours
Venue: Stadium Bukit Jalil

Registration fees for DIY Famine Camp is RM20. However, participants need to collect a minimum amount of donations (RM80-120) by using a booklet that will be given by the organiser.

Registration fees for Kidz Famine Camp is RM15. Children are required to collect a minimum of RM50 by using a donation box which will be given by the organiser as well.

For more detail, join them on www.facebook.com/group.php or forum.lowyat.net/topic/1440820

Or call, Chee Hoe at 0173585576.
